snippet.textDisplay:
Look at all the bellends thinking AJ is chinny cos he got a behind the ear shot from Ruiz. Even then Ruiz couldn't keep him down. Got up pretty quick every time.
They forget Whyte's left hook - that has literally slept men - didn't really phase AJ though he got caught with it twice. They forget he got up from a thunderous WK straight right and then withstood a two round barrage. They forget Povetkin's early assault that AJ walked through. They forget that Parker and Ruiz 2 couldn't lay a glove on him.
These casuals don't know what resilience and ringcraft is....so they massively under-rate Joshua, although he's fought every top ranked fighter willing to face him....including a couple of short notice swaps with pedigree.
He's a FAR better boxer than Wilder. He's more resilient than Wilder and he's got more power punches than Wilder - stiffer jab, harder short shots, better left.
AJ beat a tougher version of WK than Fury did. Fury knew the easy route to a title was through the massively overrated Wilder.
Fury will rightly be the favourite but AJ could beat him and deserves far more respect than he gets.
